WEBVTT

00:16.460 --> 00:18.600
{\an1}( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:22.630 --> 00:24.670
{\an1}( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:34.180 --> 00:37.120
{\an1}( <i>playing the blues )</i>

00:58.540 --> 00:59.300
{\an1}( <i>horns honking )</i>

01:03.480 --> 01:04.709
{\an1}D-OHH!

01:04.780 --> 01:07.780
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

01:18.870 --> 01:20.240
{\an1}RESIDENT, OCCUPANT.

01:20.310 --> 01:22.810
{\an1}MM. FREE SAMPLE OF LEMON TIME.

01:22.880 --> 01:23.950
{\an1}OOH, GIVE IT HERE.

01:24.010 --> 01:25.810
{\an1}( <i>gulping )</i>

01:25.880 --> 01:28.080
{\an1}\h\h\hHOMER, THAT'S
DISHWASHING LIQUID.

01:28.150 --> 01:31.390
{\an1}YEAH, BUT WHAT ARE YOU
\h\h\h\h\hGOING TO DO?

01:31.450 --> 01:34.090
{\an1}OOH! THEY'RE HAVING
A RETIREMENT PARTY

01:34.160 --> 01:35.020
{\an1}\hFOR SOMEONE
AT THE PLANT!

01:35.090 --> 01:37.130
{\an1}I WISH I COULD RETIRE.

01:37.190 --> 01:39.460
{\an1}BOY, THAT WOULD BE SWEET.

01:41.730 --> 01:43.300
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hFlanders:
HOWDY DO, NEIGHBOR.

01:43.370 --> 01:45.340
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hGOOD PIPE WEATHER.
THOUGHT I'D FIRE UP THE BRIAR.

01:45.400 --> 01:47.270
{\an1}CAN'T TALK. BUSY.

01:47.340 --> 01:48.640
{\an1}OKLEY-DOKLEY DOO.

01:48.700 --> 01:51.640
{\an1}\h\h\h\hDID YOU NOTICE
HOW SLANTED HE LOOKED?

01:51.710 --> 01:53.810
{\an1}ALL PART OF GOD'S GREAT PLAN.

01:59.820 --> 02:02.490
{\an1}I THINK ONE SIDE OF OUR HOUSE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIS SINKING.

02:08.120 --> 02:09.419
{\an1}HA HA!

02:09.490 --> 02:11.260
{\an1}"THE HALF-ASSED APPROACH

02:11.330 --> 02:13.030
{\an1}TO FOUNDATION REPAIR."

02:15.400 --> 02:17.300
{\an1}Hello, I'm Troy McClure.

02:17.370 --> 02:19.870
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hYou might remember me
from such instructional videos

02:19.940 --> 02:21.480
{\an1}as "Mothballing
Your Battleship"

02:21.540 --> 02:24.540
{\an1}and "Dig Your Own Grave
\h\h\h\h\h\hand Save".

02:24.610 --> 02:26.240
{\an1}Now, over the next six hours

02:26.310 --> 02:29.180
{\an1}I'll be taking you through
\hthe do's and do not do's

02:29.240 --> 02:30.550
{\an1}of foundation repair.

02:30.610 --> 02:31.550
{\an1}Ready?

02:31.610 --> 02:33.550
{\an1}READY.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.280
{\an1}First, patch the cracks
\h\h\h\h\h\hin the slab

02:35.350 --> 02:38.090
{\an1}using a latex patching compound
\h\h\h\hand a patching trowel.

02:38.150 --> 02:40.620
{\an1}HAND ME MY PATCHING
\h\h\hTROWEL, BOY.

02:42.020 --> 02:43.860
{\an1}HMM.

02:43.930 --> 02:46.630
{\an1}\hNow, do you have
extruded poly-vinyl
\hfoam insulation?

02:46.700 --> 02:48.210
{\an1}NO.
\h\h\h\h\h\hGood.

02:48.260 --> 02:51.270
{\an1}Assemble the aluminum J-channel
\h\husing self-furring screws.

02:51.330 --> 02:52.800
{\an1}\h\h\hInstall.
WHAT DO I...?

02:52.870 --> 02:54.970
{\an1}\h\h\hAfter applying
brushable coating...

02:55.040 --> 02:56.640
{\an1}WAIT A MINUTE.
...corrosion-resistant

02:56.710 --> 02:58.520
{\an1}metal stucco lathe.

02:58.570 --> 03:00.540
{\an1}\h\hIf you can't find
metal stucco lathe...

03:00.610 --> 03:01.980
{\an1}UH-HUH.

03:02.040 --> 03:03.710
{\an1}...use carbon fiber
\h\h\hstucco lathe.

03:03.780 --> 03:04.850
{\an1}OHH!

03:04.910 --> 03:06.480
{\an1}Now barge the lathe.

03:11.690 --> 03:13.090
{\an1}( <i>glass breaking )</i>

03:13.160 --> 03:15.630
{\an1}DID YOU SEE THE BUBBLE?

03:15.690 --> 03:18.030
{\an1}I'M AFRAID THE WHOLE WEST SIDE
\h\h\hOF YOUR HOUSE IS SINKING.

03:18.090 --> 03:19.560
{\an1}I FIGURE IT'S GONNA
\h\h\h\hCOST YOU...

03:19.630 --> 03:21.300
{\an1}OOH, 8,500.

03:21.360 --> 03:24.400
{\an1}FORGET IT! YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY
\h\h\h\hFOUNDATION GUY IN TOWN.

03:26.030 --> 03:27.640
{\an1}LET'S SEE, FOUNDATION REPAIR.

03:27.700 --> 03:29.000
{\an1}AH, HERE WE ARE...

03:29.070 --> 03:30.310
{\an1}D-OHH!

03:30.370 --> 03:32.040
{\an1}...leaving the vice president
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hin charge.

03:32.110 --> 03:35.280
{\an1}And now, leaning tower of Pisa,
\h\h\h\h\h\heat your heart out

03:35.340 --> 03:36.510
{\an1}and move over.

03:36.580 --> 03:39.150
{\an1}\h\h\h\hThis is one story
that's not on the level.

03:42.980 --> 03:46.290
{\an1}\hBEHOLD THE HORRORS
OF THE SLANTY SHANTY.

03:46.350 --> 03:48.260
{\an1}SEE THE TWISTED CREATURES
\h\h\hTHAT DWELL WITHIN.

03:48.320 --> 03:51.760
{\an1}\h\h\hMEET CUE BALL,
THE MAN WITH NO HAIR.

03:51.830 --> 03:52.830
{\an1}HUH?

03:52.890 --> 03:54.200
{\an1}( <i>growling )</i>

03:54.260 --> 03:55.200
{\an1}( <i>gasping )</i>

03:55.260 --> 03:56.300
{\an1}HE'S HIDEOUS!

03:58.970 --> 04:01.900
{\an1}WE HAVE TO DO SOMETHING.

04:01.970 --> 04:04.570
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMARGE,
IT WILL COST $8,500.

04:04.640 --> 04:08.180
{\an1}WE ONLY HAVE 500 IN THE
BANK, AND THAT LEAVES...

04:08.240 --> 04:09.580
{\an1}80 HUNDRED WE NEED.

04:09.640 --> 04:10.780
{\an1}I COULD GET A JOB.

04:10.850 --> 04:11.780
{\an1}HEY...

04:11.850 --> 04:13.920
{\an1}THEN I COULD FOLLOW MY DREAM:

04:13.980 --> 04:18.890
{\an1}LIVING IN THE WOODS AND KEEPING
\h\h\hA JOURNAL OF MY THOUGHTS.

04:18.950 --> 04:22.260
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h <i>MARCH 15--
I WISH I'D BROUGHT A TV.</i>

04:22.320 --> 04:25.430
{\an1}<i>OH, GOD, HOW I MISS TV.</i>

04:27.760 --> 04:29.760
{\an1}\h\h\hI THINK YOU HAVE
TO KEEP YOUR JOB, TOO.

04:29.830 --> 04:30.700
{\an1}AW!

04:34.500 --> 04:36.470
{\an1}\h\hIT WAS THE
MOST BEAUTIFUL

04:36.540 --> 04:38.740
{\an1}\hMOST EXPENSIVE
TRAIN EVER BUILT.

04:38.810 --> 04:40.840
{\an1}THE SPRUCE CABOOSE.

04:40.910 --> 04:44.050
{\an1}SOME PEOPLE SAID IT WAS TOO BIG
\h\h\h\hTO STAY ON THE TRACKS.

04:44.110 --> 04:46.150
{\an1}HEH HEH, THEY WERE RIGHT.

04:46.210 --> 04:48.080
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWE'RE HERE
FOR THE RETIREMENT PARTY.

04:48.150 --> 04:49.780
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFOLLOW
THE HEADLESS BRAKEMAN.

04:49.850 --> 04:51.490
{\an1}POWER PLANT RETIREMENT PARTY.

04:51.550 --> 04:53.660
{\an1}OW! RIGHT THIS WAY.
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h( <i>glass shatters )</i>

04:53.720 --> 04:55.560
{\an1}OW!

04:55.620 --> 04:56.760
{\an1}( <i>clearing throat )</i>

04:56.830 --> 05:00.610
{\an1}AHEM. TONIGHT, WE'VE ALL
\h\h\h\h\hCOME TO HONOR

05:00.660 --> 05:03.060
{\an1}A CLOSE FRIEND OF OURS.

05:03.130 --> 05:04.270
{\an1}BORING.

05:04.330 --> 05:07.070
{\an1}\hA MAN WHO PROVIDED
THE BURNS CORPORATION

05:07.140 --> 05:09.000
{\an1}\h\h\h\hWITH 45 YEARS
OF FAITHFUL SERVICE--

05:09.070 --> 05:10.940
{\an1}MR. JACK MARLEY.

05:11.010 --> 05:12.040
{\an1}BORING.

05:12.110 --> 05:13.810
{\an1}( <i>angry muttering )</i>

05:13.880 --> 05:15.180
{\an1}MR. BURNS,
IF YOU DON'T MIND,

05:15.240 --> 05:16.510
{\an1}I'VE PREPARED
A LITTLE MUSICAL NUMBER

05:16.580 --> 05:18.310
{\an1}FOR JACK'S SPECIAL NIGHT.

05:21.580 --> 05:22.620
{\an1}♪ THERE IS A MAN ♪

05:22.680 --> 05:23.580
{\an1}♪ <i>THERE IS A MAN ♪</i>

05:23.650 --> 05:24.650
{\an1}♪ A CERTAIN MAN ♪

05:24.720 --> 05:25.990
{\an1}♪ <i>A CERTAIN MAN ♪</i>

05:26.050 --> 05:27.060
{\an1}♪ A MAN WHOSE GRACE
AND HANDSOME FACE ♪

05:27.120 --> 05:29.120
{\an1}♪ ARE KNOWN ACROSS THE LAND ♪

05:29.190 --> 05:30.090
{\an1}♪ YOU KNOW HIS NAME ♪

05:30.160 --> 05:31.690
{\an1}♪ <i>YOU KNOW HIS NAME ♪</i>

05:31.760 --> 05:32.590
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h♪ IT'S MR. BURNS ♪
♪ <i>IT'S MR. BURNS ♪</i>

05:32.660 --> 05:33.800
{\an1}♪ HE LOVES A SMOKE ♪

05:33.860 --> 05:35.560
{\an1}♪ ENJOYS A JOKE ♪

05:35.630 --> 05:39.100
{\an1}♪ WHY, HE'S WORTH TEN TIMES
\h\h\h\h\h\hWHAT HE EARNS ♪

05:39.170 --> 05:40.600
{\an1}♪ <i>HE'S MR. BURNS ♪
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI'M MR. BURNS.</i>

05:40.670 --> 05:41.500
{\an1}HE'S MONTY BURNS.

05:41.570 --> 05:42.900
{\an1}I'M <i>MR. BURNS.</i>

05:42.970 --> 05:44.670
{\an1}\h\h\h\h♪ TO FRIENDS,
HE'S KNOWN AS MONTY ♪

05:44.740 --> 05:48.410
{\an1}\h\h♪ BUT TO YOU,
IT'S MR. BURNS ♪

05:48.480 --> 05:49.910
{\an1}♪ BUR-BUR-BUR-BUR-BURNS ♪

05:49.980 --> 05:51.250
{\an1}BURNS!

05:51.310 --> 05:53.110
{\an1}YOU MIND IF I SAY
\h\hA FEW WORDS?

05:53.180 --> 05:54.680
{\an1}( <i>mockingly: )
OH, ME, ME, ME.</i>

05:54.750 --> 05:56.020
{\an1}\hI NEED ALL
THE ATTENTION

05:56.080 --> 05:57.890
{\an1}JUST BECAUSE IT'S
\h\hMY PARTY, EH?

05:57.950 --> 05:59.550
{\an1}( <i>dismissive grunt )</i>

05:59.620 --> 06:01.260
{\an1}PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME RETIRE.

06:01.320 --> 06:03.360
{\an1}MY JOB IS THE ONLY THING
\hTHAT KEEPS ME ALIVE.

06:03.430 --> 06:06.500
{\an1}\h\hI NEVER MARRIED,
AND MY DOG IS DEAD...

06:06.560 --> 06:07.830
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h( <i>"For He's
A Jolly Good Fellow" )</i>

06:07.900 --> 06:08.900
{\an1}I'M NOT FINISHED!

06:08.960 --> 06:11.470
{\an1}OH, YES, YOU ARE.

06:15.140 --> 06:16.240
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

06:18.070 --> 06:20.070
{\an1}WITH THE DEPARTURE
\h\h\hOF MR. MARLEY

06:20.140 --> 06:21.710
{\an1}\h\h\hTHERE WILL NOW BE
AN ENTRY LEVEL POSITION

06:21.780 --> 06:23.440
{\an1}OPEN IN SECTOR 7-G.

06:23.510 --> 06:24.810
{\an1}\h\h\hNOW GET OUT.
THE BAR IS CLOSED.

06:24.880 --> 06:25.980
{\an1}( <i>all moan )</i>

06:27.850 --> 06:29.550
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hMarge:
\h\hMAYBE I SHOULD
APPLY FOR THAT JOB.

06:29.620 --> 06:30.590
{\an1}FORGET IT, MARGE.

06:30.650 --> 06:32.150
{\an1}WE ALREADY LIVE TOGETHER.

06:32.220 --> 06:33.420
{\an1}WE SHOULDN'T WORK TOGETHER.

06:33.490 --> 06:34.960
{\an1}AS THE BIBLE SAYS,

06:35.020 --> 06:38.130
{\an1}\h"THOU SHALT NOT HORN IN
ON THY HUSBAND'S RACKET."

06:38.190 --> 06:39.890
{\an1}WHERE DOES THE BIBLE
\h\h\h\h\hSAY RACKET?

06:39.960 --> 06:41.460
{\an1}IT'S IN THERE.

06:41.530 --> 06:44.470
{\an1}LOOK, MARGE WE JUST DON'T
NEED THE MONEY THAT BAD.

06:49.470 --> 06:51.510
{\an1}W-AHH!
( grunts )

06:59.050 --> 07:01.320
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hWELL, LISA,
I FINISHED MY RESUME.

07:04.850 --> 07:07.490
{\an1}UH, I THINK IT NEEDS
\h\hA LITTLE PADDING.

07:10.060 --> 07:11.760
{\an1}\h\hWHAT ARE YOU
PUTTING IN THERE?

07:11.830 --> 07:12.760
{\an1}BUP, BUP, BUP.

07:12.830 --> 07:15.300
{\an1}WHEN I'M DONE.

07:16.630 --> 07:19.900
{\an1}CHAUFFEUR, SEAMSTRESS.

07:19.970 --> 07:21.970
{\an1}CURATOR OF LARGE MAMMALS?

07:22.040 --> 07:25.240
{\an1}MARGE, HAVE YOU SEEN
\h\h\h\hMY LUNCH BOX?

07:25.310 --> 07:27.780
{\an1}OH, I SEE.

07:27.840 --> 07:30.550
{\an1}MOM, THEY EXPECT YOU
\h\hTO LIE A LITTLE.

07:30.610 --> 07:32.850
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWORKED FOR
THE CARTER ADMINISTRATION?!

07:32.910 --> 07:34.780
{\an1}WELL, YOU VOTED
FOR HIM TWICE.

07:34.850 --> 07:36.880
{\an1}LISA, SHH. SOMEONE MIGHT BE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLISTENING.

07:36.950 --> 07:37.920
{\an1}MM-HMM.

07:37.990 --> 07:39.120
{\an1}UH-HUH.

07:39.190 --> 07:41.820
{\an1}I THOUGHT MUDDY WATERS
\h\h\hWROTE THAT SONG.

07:41.890 --> 07:42.990
{\an1}( <i>groans )</i>

07:43.060 --> 07:45.630
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTHIS RESUME
IS VERY IMPRESSIVE.

07:45.690 --> 07:47.900
{\an1}LET ME BE THE FIRST TO SAY
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h <i>KABEBU KAZINI.</i>

07:47.960 --> 07:48.900
{\an1}WHAT?

07:48.960 --> 07:51.070
{\an1}WELCOME ABOARD.

07:51.130 --> 07:53.100
{\an1}\h\h\hI GUESS MY SWAHILI
IS NOT AS GOOD AS YOURS.

07:53.170 --> 07:54.470
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

07:54.540 --> 07:55.640
{\an1}YEAH, HMM.

07:55.700 --> 07:56.970
{\an1}SORRY.

07:57.040 --> 07:58.610
{\an1}THE POSITION HAS BEEN FILLED.

07:58.670 --> 08:00.110
{\an1}( <i>grumbling )</i>

08:00.180 --> 08:01.620
{\an1}OH, DEAR.

08:01.680 --> 08:04.180
{\an1}MARGE, YOU'RE MAKING
\h\hA BIG MISTAKE.

08:04.250 --> 08:06.880
{\an1}I'M GONNA SEE YOU ALL DAY
\h\hAT WORK AND ALL NIGHT
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAT HOME...

08:06.950 --> 08:07.880
{\an1}MMM!

08:07.950 --> 08:09.550
{\an1}AND THAT'S GOOD.

08:09.620 --> 08:11.520
{\an1}BUT HERE'S THE BAD PART:

08:11.590 --> 08:13.220
{\an1}UH, UH...

08:13.290 --> 08:15.890
{\an1}OOH, LOOK AT THAT HEADLINE.

08:15.960 --> 08:17.690
{\an1}"CANADA TO HOLD REFERENDUM."

08:17.760 --> 08:18.690
{\an1}\hSORRY, MARGE,
CAN'T TALK NOW.

08:18.760 --> 08:20.130
{\an1}WE NEED THE MONEY.

08:20.200 --> 08:21.940
{\an1}AND MY LIFE IS PRETTY BORING.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.870
{\an1}\hLAST WEEK, SOME JEHOVAH'S
WITNESSES CAME TO THE DOOR,

08:24.930 --> 08:26.530
{\an1}AND I WOULDN'T
LET THEM LEAVE.

08:26.600 --> 08:28.200
{\an1}THEY SNUCK AWAY WHEN
I WENT IN THE KITCHEN

08:28.270 --> 08:29.600
{\an1}TO GET MORE LEMONADE.

08:29.670 --> 08:31.440
{\an1}YEAH, LEMONADE IS GOOD.

08:31.510 --> 08:32.909
{\an1}I THINK IT'S WONDERFUL.

08:32.970 --> 08:36.240
{\an1}MOM AND DAD, SIDE-BY-SIDE
\h\h\hAT THE POWER PLANT.

08:36.309 --> 08:38.010
{\an1}\h\hYOU'LL BE JUST LIKE
MARIE AND PIERRE CURIE.

08:38.080 --> 08:39.549
{\an1}WHAT DID THEY DO?

08:39.610 --> 08:41.220
{\an1}THEY DISCOVERED RADIUM.

08:41.280 --> 08:44.020
{\an1}\h\hTHEN THEY BOTH DIED
OF RADIATION POISONING.

08:44.090 --> 08:45.220
{\an1}HMM.

08:46.650 --> 08:48.890
{\an1}( <i>roaring )</i>

08:48.960 --> 08:52.530
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

08:52.590 --> 08:54.360
{\an1}IT'S THE CURIES.
\h\hWE MUST FLEE.

09:01.170 --> 09:02.340
{\an1}COOL!

09:03.910 --> 09:05.340
{\an1}\h\hNOW, MARGE,
JUST REMEMBER.

09:05.410 --> 09:07.510
{\an1}IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG
\h\h\h\h\hAT THE PLANT,

09:07.580 --> 09:09.610
{\an1}\h\hBLAME THE GUY WHO
CAN'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

09:09.680 --> 09:16.180
{\an1}AH, TIBOR, HOW MANY TIMES
\hHAVE YOU SAVED MY BUTT?

09:16.250 --> 09:18.350
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMAGGIE,
YOUR BABY-SITTER'S HERE.

09:19.750 --> 09:21.060
{\an1}WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

09:21.120 --> 09:22.420
{\an1}WHOA!

09:22.490 --> 09:23.690
{\an1}YOU MUST BE SICK.

09:23.760 --> 09:24.990
{\an1}LET'S SEE.

09:25.060 --> 09:26.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hWHAT'S OLD
DOC WASHBURN PRESCRIBE?

09:26.800 --> 09:28.310
{\an1}DO YOU HAVE DROPSY?

09:28.360 --> 09:30.230
{\an1}THE GRIPPE?
SCOPULA?

09:30.300 --> 09:31.970
{\an1}THE VAPORS?
JUNGLE ROT?

09:32.030 --> 09:34.140
{\an1}\h\hSHANTY FEVER?
POOR MAN'S GOUT?

09:34.200 --> 09:38.140
{\an1}HOUSEMAID'S KNEE?
CLIMACTIC BOUBA?

09:38.210 --> 09:40.710
{\an1}THE STAGGERS?
DUM-DUM FEVER?

09:41.910 --> 09:43.580
{\an1}AND THIS IS YOUR OFFICE.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.820
{\an1}THAT IDIOT TIBOR
\h\hLOST THE KEY

09:45.880 --> 09:48.580
{\an1}\h\hBUT YOU CAN JIMMY IT
OPEN WITH A CREDIT CARD.

09:48.650 --> 09:49.820
{\an1}( <i>computer whirring )</i>

09:49.880 --> 09:51.390
{\an1}WELL, HAVE FUN.

09:51.450 --> 09:53.090
{\an1}WHAT DO I DO?

09:53.150 --> 09:55.990
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hMARGE, PLEASE,
ACCORDING TO YOUR RESUME

09:56.060 --> 09:58.330
{\an1}YOU INVENTED
THIS MACHINE.

09:58.390 --> 10:00.030
{\an1}( <i>electronic humming )</i>

10:01.800 --> 10:03.860
{\an1}( <i>explosion, men shouting )</i>

10:08.340 --> 10:09.470
{\an1}PUT AWAY YOUR BOOKS,
\h\h\h\h\h\hCHILDREN.

10:09.540 --> 10:11.410
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIT'S TIME
FOR YOUR ENGLISH TEST.

10:11.470 --> 10:12.710
{\an1}( <i>moaning )</i>

10:14.680 --> 10:16.810
{\an1}SICK ON TEST DAY.

10:16.880 --> 10:19.580
{\an1}WHY? WHY?

10:19.650 --> 10:21.980
{\an1}\h\hBART HAVE YOU READ
<i>THE BOY WHO CRIED WOLF?</i>

10:22.050 --> 10:23.450
{\an1}I'M HALFWAY THROUGH IT.

10:23.520 --> 10:24.520
{\an1}I SWEAR.

10:24.590 --> 10:26.590
{\an1}( <i>groaning )</i>

10:28.360 --> 10:29.360
{\an1}( <i>door slams )</i>

10:29.420 --> 10:30.320
{\an1}( <i>scoffs )</i>

10:31.590 --> 10:33.360
{\an1}MARGE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:33.430 --> 10:34.700
